title: For Sale:  AR15 Cut-Away !!
postcontent: Now you can have a cut-away AR15 of your very own!Buy before December 10 for Xmas delivery!Lots of gun folks are fascinated not just with shooting guns, but also how they function. Being able to actually see the internal workings is even better.The cut-away started off as a new rifle. The barrel, gas block, lower receiver, upper receiver, stock, buffer tube, pistol grip and magazine have machined cutouts so you can see the internal parts and their movements as the gun cycles.The bolt carrier group and charging handle are fully operational and can be manually cycled along with the trigger and selector. The functionality of the lower is fully maintained, so the rifle is transferred as a firearm, as per all federal and state laws.Since the barrel has been cut open, firing the upper is a no-no. A dummy round is glued in the chamber to illustrate cartridge placement in the chamber and barrel, as well as to block the barrel, preventing it from being loaded with live ammunition.Comes with 10 dummy rounds for display in magazine.This is great for wall art and is a perfect instructional tool as well!Will ship for $20

title: For Sale:   	IBIS Tek Ford Crown Victora Ballistic door panels Level III not level llla
postcontent: Ibis Tek NIJ Level III ballistic (2) panels 2 front-----  Be sure to read up on what NIJ level III means. ======READ THIS https://justnet.org/compliant/additional-information-cpl.html====== to verify what these panels are rated and what it means. These panels offer greater protection than level IIIa, a common mistake people make.  Here is the installation guide=====https://www.flickr.com/photos/houstonpappas/albums/72157675043105590  It is much more capable of stopping MORE higher velocity, more powerful rounds than what is worn, except for the BEST of riot gear (level IV) that stops armor piercing 30.06 (M2ap). This armor is just the level below IV which is protection against specified armor piercing rounds.   These are steel plates, not ceramic like ford OEM, and others that only lasts a few years because it cracks and only can with stand limited hits. I think the weight is 22lbs each.  Ck laws in your state for restrictions. Convicted felons and probably others are probably prohibited from ownership/possession.  Have 2 Ibis TEK NIJ Level III panels (both front doors) for Crown Victoria. Currently installed on 2010 CVPI. Includes both panels and removed mounting hardware and Ibs Tek installation instructions. Excellent condition, never shot, but will have some scuff marks/light rust probably, as they are currently installed.  If your are not familar with installation, you will need to remove the glass and window regulator, which requires 1/4" (I think) rivets. If you have done that before, this installation is a snap. A couple of holes need to be drilled in the rear panel of each door, near the bottom for a one of the brackets.  PM for jpg of installation instructions if you are a serious, about purchasing these ballistic panels.
